public static <T> void permute(T[] a,
                               Comparator<T> comp,
                               int fromIndex,
                               int toIndex)
Takes an array a and rearranges it into the next permutation in lexicographic order. Use an algorithm defined in http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation#Generation_in_lexicographic_order which probably isnt the most efficient solution.

Parameters:
a - the array to be permuted
toIndex - index of the first element (inclusive) to be permuted
fromIndex - index of the last element (exclusive) to be permuted
